Abdomen at least slightly wider than elytra; anterior tergites without sexual dimorphism; punctation moderately fine and moderately sparse on anterior tergites, very fine and very sparse on posterior tergites; posterior margin of tergite VII without palisade fringe; posterior margin of tergite VIII weakly convex in both sexes (
Fig. 44
).

